1. playbooks are a list of plays.
2. plays are list of tasks.
3. tasks are module or command executed.

playbooks and plays are written using yaml format.
yaml only contains of list and dictionaries.
2 rules of writing yaml file.
if items do not belong to each other will be on same level.
child items will be indented along with the parent.

wsriting playbook - playbook.yml
yaml file starts with ---
'-' single dash means start of the list.
'...' end of the playbooknfile.
# after writing the playbooks run ansible-playbook playbook.yml --syntax-check

syntax check will only check the playbook.
indentation warning,


